alert.note: Alert for Dripping Springs; Pinal, Superstition Mountains (Arizona) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Phoenix (Central Arizona and California Desert)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 13 at 1:44PM MST until February 14 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Phoenix
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM TO 11 PM MST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. * WHERE...Pinal/Superstition Mountains and Dripping Springs. * WHEN...From 2 PM to 11 PM MST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Very difficult driving conditions, especially for larger vehicles traveling along roads with crosswinds. Light, unsecured objects will become airborne. Moderate tree and minor structural damage possible.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage. In addition, strong winds over desert areas could result in briefly lowered visibilities to well under a mile at times in blowing dust or blowing sand. Use extra caution.
